148RenderPtr<RenderElement> RenderElement::createFor(Element& element, RenderStyle&& style, OptionSet<ConstructBlockLevelRendererFor> rendererTypeOverride)
149{
150 // Minimal support for content properties replacing an entire element.
151 // Works only if we have exactly one piece of content and it's a URL.
152 // Otherwise acts as if we didn't support this feature.
153 const ContentData* contentData = style.contentData();
154 if (!rendererTypeOverride && contentData && !contentData->next() && is<ImageContentData>(*contentData) && !element.isPseudoElement()) {
155 Style::loadPendingResources(style, element.document(), &element);
156 auto& styleImage = downcast<ImageContentData>(*contentData).image();
157 auto image = createRenderer<RenderImage>(element, WTFMove(style), const_cast<StyleImage*>(&styleImage));
158 image->setIsGeneratedContent();
159 return image;
160 }
161
162 switch (style.display()) {
163 case DisplayType::None:
164 case DisplayType::Contents:
165 return nullptr;
166 case DisplayType::Inline:
167 if (rendererTypeOverride.contains(ConstructBlockLevelRendererFor::Inline))
168 return createRenderer<RenderBlockFlow>(element, WTFMove(style));
169 return createRenderer<RenderInline>(element, WTFMove(style));
170 case DisplayType::Block:
171 case DisplayType::FlowRoot:
172 case DisplayType::InlineBlock:
173 return createRenderer<RenderBlockFlow>(element, WTFMove(style));
174 case DisplayType::ListItem:
175 if (rendererTypeOverride.contains(ConstructBlockLevelRendererFor::ListItem))
176 return createRenderer<RenderBlockFlow>(element, WTFMove(style));
177 return createRenderer<RenderListItem>(element, WTFMove(style));
178 case DisplayType::Flex:
179 case DisplayType::InlineFlex:
180 return createRenderer<RenderFlexibleBox>(element, WTFMove(style));
181 case DisplayType::Grid:
182 case DisplayType::InlineGrid:
183 return createRenderer<RenderGrid>(element, WTFMove(style));
184 case DisplayType::Box:
185 case DisplayType::InlineBox:
186 return createRenderer<RenderDeprecatedFlexibleBox>(element, WTFMove(style));
187 default: {
188 if (style.isDisplayTableOrTablePart() && rendererTypeOverride.contains(ConstructBlockLevelRendererFor::TableOrTablePart))
189 return createRenderer<RenderBlockFlow>(element, WTFMove(style));
190
191 switch (style.display()) {
192 case DisplayType::Table:
193 case DisplayType::InlineTable:
194 return createRenderer<RenderTable>(element, WTFMove(style));
195 case DisplayType::TableCell:
196 return createRenderer<RenderTableCell>(element, WTFMove(style));
197 case DisplayType::TableCaption:
198 return createRenderer<RenderTableCaption>(element, WTFMove(style));
199 case DisplayType::TableRowGroup:
200 case DisplayType::TableHeaderGroup:
201 case DisplayType::TableFooterGroup:
202 return createRenderer<RenderTableSection>(element, WTFMove(style));
203 case DisplayType::TableRow:
204 return createRenderer<RenderTableRow>(element, WTFMove(style));
205 case DisplayType::TableColumnGroup:
206 case DisplayType::TableColumn:
207 return createRenderer<RenderTableCol>(element, WTFMove(style));
208 default:
209 break;
210 }
211 break;
212 }
213 }
214 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
215 return nullptr;
216}

218std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> RenderElement::computeFirstLineStyle() const
219{
220 ASSERT(view().usesFirstLineRules());
221
222 RenderElement& rendererForFirstLineStyle = isBeforeOrAfterContent() ? *parent() : const_cast<RenderElement&>(*this);
223
224 if (rendererForFirstLineStyle.isRenderBlockFlow() || rendererForFirstLineStyle.isRenderButton()) {
225 RenderBlock* firstLineBlock = rendererForFirstLineStyle.firstLineBlock();
226 if (!firstLineBlock)
227 return nullptr;
228 auto* firstLineStyle = firstLineBlock->getCachedPseudoStyle(PseudoId::FirstLine, &style());
229 if (!firstLineStyle)
230 return nullptr;
231 return RenderStyle::clonePtr(*firstLineStyle);
232 }
233
234 if (!rendererForFirstLineStyle.isRenderInline())
235 return nullptr;
236
237 auto& parentStyle = rendererForFirstLineStyle.parent()->firstLineStyle();
238 if (&parentStyle == &rendererForFirstLineStyle.parent()->style())
239 return nullptr;
240
241 if (rendererForFirstLineStyle.isAnonymous()) {
242 auto* textRendererWithDisplayContentsParent = RenderText::findByDisplayContentsInlineWrapperCandidate(rendererForFirstLineStyle);
243 if (!textRendererWithDisplayContentsParent)
244 return nullptr;
245 auto* composedTreeParentElement = textRendererWithDisplayContentsParent->textNode()->parentElementInComposedTree();
246 if (!composedTreeParentElement)
247 return nullptr;
248
249 auto style = composedTreeParentElement->styleResolver().styleForElement(*composedTreeParentElement, &parentStyle).renderStyle;
250 ASSERT(style->display() == DisplayType::Contents);
251
252 // We act as if there was an unstyled <span> around the text node. Only styling happens via inheritance.
253 auto firstLineStyle = RenderStyle::createPtr();
254 firstLineStyle->inheritFrom(*style);
255 return firstLineStyle;
256 }
257
258 return rendererForFirstLineStyle.element()->styleResolver().styleForElement(*element(), &parentStyle).renderStyle;
259}
260
261const RenderStyle& RenderElement::firstLineStyle() const
262{
263 if (!view().usesFirstLineRules())
264 return style();
265
266 if (!m_hasValidCachedFirstLineStyle) {
267 auto firstLineStyle = computeFirstLineStyle();
268 if (firstLineStyle || hasRareData())
269 const_cast<RenderElement&>(*this).ensureRareData().cachedFirstLineStyle = WTFMove(firstLineStyle);
270 m_hasValidCachedFirstLineStyle = true;
271 }
272
273 return (hasRareData() && rareData().cachedFirstLineStyle) ? *rareData().cachedFirstLineStyle : style();
274}

276StyleDifference RenderElement::adjustStyleDifference(StyleDifference diff, OptionSet<StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty> contextSensitiveProperties) const
277{
278 // If transform changed, and we are not composited, need to do a layout.
279 if (contextSensitiveProperties & StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty::Transform) {
280 // FIXME: when transforms are taken into account for overflow, we will need to do a layout.
281 if (!hasLayer() || !downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this).layer()->isComposited()) {
282 if (!hasLayer())
283 diff = std::max(diff, StyleDifference::Layout);
284 else {
285 // We need to set at least SimplifiedLayout, but if PositionedMovementOnly is already set
286 // then we actually need SimplifiedLayoutAndPositionedMovement.
287 diff = std::max(diff, (diff == StyleDifference::LayoutPositionedMovementOnly) ? StyleDifference::SimplifiedLayoutAndPositionedMovement : StyleDifference::SimplifiedLayout);
288 }
289
290 } else
291 diff = std::max(diff, StyleDifference::RecompositeLayer);
292 }
293
294 if (contextSensitiveProperties & StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty::Opacity) {
295 if (!hasLayer() || !downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this).layer()->isComposited())
296 diff = std::max(diff, StyleDifference::RepaintLayer);
297 else
298 diff = std::max(diff, StyleDifference::RecompositeLayer);
299 }
300
301 if (contextSensitiveProperties & StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty::ClipPath) {
302 if (hasLayer()
303 && downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this).layer()->isComposited()
304 && hasClipPath()
305 && RenderLayerCompositor::canCompositeClipPath(*downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this).layer()))
306 diff = std::max(diff, StyleDifference::RecompositeLayer);
307 else
308 diff = std::max(diff, StyleDifference::Repaint);
309 }
310
311 if (contextSensitiveProperties & StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty::WillChange) {
312 if (style().willChange() && style().willChange()->canTriggerCompositing())
313 diff = std::max(diff, StyleDifference::RecompositeLayer);
314 }
315
316 if ((contextSensitiveProperties & StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty::Filter) && hasLayer()) {
317 auto& layer = *downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this).layer();
318 if (!layer.isComposited() || layer.paintsWithFilters())
319 diff = std::max(diff, StyleDifference::RepaintLayer);
320 else
321 diff = std::max(diff, StyleDifference::RecompositeLayer);
322 }
323
324 // The answer to requiresLayer() for plugins, iframes, and canvas can change without the actual
325 // style changing, since it depends on whether we decide to composite these elements. When the
326 // layer status of one of these elements changes, we need to force a layout.
327 if (diff < StyleDifference::Layout && isRenderLayerModelObject()) {
328 if (hasLayer() != downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this).requiresLayer())
329 diff = StyleDifference::Layout;
330 }
331
332 // If we have no layer(), just treat a RepaintLayer hint as a normal Repaint.
333 if (diff == StyleDifference::RepaintLayer && !hasLayer())
334 diff = StyleDifference::Repaint;
335
336 return diff;
337}

339inline bool RenderElement::hasImmediateNonWhitespaceTextChildOrBorderOrOutline() const
340{
341 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<RenderObject>(*this)) {
342 if (is<RenderText>(child) && !downcast<RenderText>(child).isAllCollapsibleWhitespace())
343 return true;
344 if (child.style().hasOutline() || child.style().hasBorder())
345 return true;
346 }
347 return false;
348}
349
350inline bool RenderElement::shouldRepaintForStyleDifference(StyleDifference diff) const
351{
352 return diff == StyleDifference::Repaint || (diff == StyleDifference::RepaintIfTextOrBorderOrOutline && hasImmediateNonWhitespaceTextChildOrBorderOrOutline());
353}

355void RenderElement::updateFillImages(const FillLayer* oldLayers, const FillLayer& newLayers)
356{
357 auto fillImagesAreIdentical = [](const FillLayer* layer1, const FillLayer* layer2) -> bool {
358 if (layer1 == layer2)
359 return true;
360
361 for (; layer1 && layer2; layer1 = layer1->next(), layer2 = layer2->next()) {
362 if (!arePointingToEqualData(layer1->image(), layer2->image()))
363 return false;
364 if (layer1->image() && layer1->image()->usesDataProtocol())
365 return false;
366 }
367
368 return !layer1 && !layer2;
369 };
370
371 auto isRegisteredWithNewFillImages = [&]() -> bool {
372 for (auto* layer = &newLayers; layer; layer = layer->next()) {
373 if (layer->image() && !layer->image()->hasClient(*this))
374 return false;
375 }
376 return true;
377 };
378
379 // If images have the same characteristics and this element is already registered as a
380 // client to the new images, there is nothing to do.
381 if (fillImagesAreIdentical(oldLayers, &newLayers) && isRegisteredWithNewFillImages())
382 return;
383
384 // Add before removing, to avoid removing all clients of an image that is in both sets.
385 for (auto* layer = &newLayers; layer; layer = layer->next()) {
386 if (layer->image())
387 layer->image()->addClient(*this);
388 }
389 for (auto* layer = oldLayers; layer; layer = layer->next()) {
390 if (layer->image())
391 layer->image()->removeClient(*this);
392 }
393}
394
395void RenderElement::updateImage(StyleImage* oldImage, StyleImage* newImage)
396{
397 if (oldImage == newImage)
398 return;
399 if (oldImage)
400 oldImage->removeClient(*this);
401 if (newImage)
402 newImage->addClient(*this);
403}

405void RenderElement::updateShapeImage(const ShapeValue* oldShapeValue, const ShapeValue* newShapeValue)
406{
407 if (oldShapeValue || newShapeValue)
408 updateImage(oldShapeValue ? oldShapeValue->image() : nullptr, newShapeValue ? newShapeValue->image() : nullptr);
409}

411bool RenderElement::repaintBeforeStyleChange(StyleDifference diff, const RenderStyle& oldStyle, const RenderStyle& newStyle)
412{
413 if (oldStyle.visibility() == Visibility::Hidden) {
414 // Repaint on hidden renderer is a no-op.
415 return false;
416 }
417 enum class RequiredRepaint { None, RendererOnly, RendererAndDescendantsRenderersWithLayers };
418 auto shouldRepaintBeforeStyleChange = [&]() -> RequiredRepaint {
419 if (!parent()) {
420 // Can't resolve absolute coordinates.
421 return RequiredRepaint::None;
422 }
423
424 if (is<RenderLayerModelObject>(this) && hasLayer()) {
425 if (diff == StyleDifference::RepaintLayer)
426 return RequiredRepaint::RendererAndDescendantsRenderersWithLayers;
427
428 if (diff == StyleDifference::Layout || diff == StyleDifference::SimplifiedLayout) {
429 // Certain style changes require layer repaint, since the layer could end up being destroyed.
430 auto layerMayGetDestroyed = oldStyle.position() != newStyle.position()
431 || oldStyle.usedZIndex() != newStyle.usedZIndex()
432 || oldStyle.hasAutoUsedZIndex() != newStyle.hasAutoUsedZIndex()
433 || oldStyle.clip() != newStyle.clip()
434 || oldStyle.hasClip() != newStyle.hasClip()
435 || oldStyle.hasOpacity() != newStyle.hasOpacity()
436 || oldStyle.hasTransform() != newStyle.hasTransform()
437 || oldStyle.hasFilter() != newStyle.hasFilter();
438 if (layerMayGetDestroyed)
439 return RequiredRepaint::RendererAndDescendantsRenderersWithLayers;
440 }
441 }
442
443 if (shouldRepaintForStyleDifference(diff))
444 return RequiredRepaint::RendererOnly;
445
446 if (newStyle.outlineSize() < oldStyle.outlineSize())
447 return RequiredRepaint::RendererOnly;
448
449 if (is<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this)) {
450 // If we don't have a layer yet, but we are going to get one because of transform or opacity, then we need to repaint the old position of the object.
451 bool hasLayer = downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this).hasLayer();
452 bool willHaveLayer = newStyle.hasTransform() || newStyle.hasOpacity() || newStyle.hasFilter() || newStyle.hasBackdropFilter();
453 if (!hasLayer && willHaveLayer)
454 return RequiredRepaint::RendererOnly;
455 }
456
457 if (is<RenderBox>(*this)) {
458 if (diff == StyleDifference::Layout && oldStyle.position() != newStyle.position() && oldStyle.position() == PositionType::Static)
459 return RequiredRepaint::RendererOnly;
460 }
461
462 if (diff > StyleDifference::RepaintLayer && oldStyle.visibility() != newStyle.visibility()) {
463 if (auto* enclosingLayer = this->enclosingLayer()) {
464 auto rendererWillBeHidden = newStyle.visibility() != Visibility::Visible;
465 if (rendererWillBeHidden && enclosingLayer->hasVisibleContent() && (this == &enclosingLayer->renderer() || enclosingLayer->renderer().style().visibility() != Visibility::Visible))
466 return RequiredRepaint::RendererOnly;
467 }
468 }
469
470 return RequiredRepaint::None;
471 }();
472
473 if (shouldRepaintBeforeStyleChange == RequiredRepaint::RendererAndDescendantsRenderersWithLayers) {
474 ASSERT(hasLayer());
475 downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this).layer()->repaintIncludingDescendants();
476 return true;
477 }
478
479 if (shouldRepaintBeforeStyleChange == RequiredRepaint::RendererOnly) {
480 repaint();
481 return true;
482 }
483
484 return false;
485}

487void RenderElement::initializeStyle()
488{
489 Style::loadPendingResources(m_style, document(), element());
490
491 styleWillChange(StyleDifference::NewStyle, style());
492 m_hasInitializedStyle = true;
493 styleDidChange(StyleDifference::NewStyle, nullptr);
494
495 // We shouldn't have any text children that would need styleDidChange at this point.
496 ASSERT(!childrenOfType<RenderText>(*this).first());
497
498 // It would be nice to assert that !parent() here, but some RenderLayer subrenderers
499 // have their parent set before getting a call to initializeStyle() :|
500}
501
502void RenderElement::setStyle(RenderStyle&& style, StyleDifference minimalStyleDifference)
503{
504 // FIXME: Should change RenderView so it can use initializeStyle too.
505 // If we do that, we can assert m_hasInitializedStyle unconditionally,
506 // and remove the check of m_hasInitializedStyle below too.
507 ASSERT(m_hasInitializedStyle || isRenderView());
508
509 StyleDifference diff = StyleDifference::Equal;
510 OptionSet<StyleDifferenceContextSensitiveProperty> contextSensitiveProperties;
511 if (m_hasInitializedStyle)
512 diff = m_style.diff(style, contextSensitiveProperties);
513
514 diff = std::max(diff, minimalStyleDifference);
515
516 diff = adjustStyleDifference(diff, contextSensitiveProperties);
517
518 Style::loadPendingResources(style, document(), element());
519
520 auto didRepaint = repaintBeforeStyleChange(diff, m_style, style);
521 styleWillChange(diff, style);
522 auto oldStyle = m_style.replace(WTFMove(style));
523 bool detachedFromParent = !parent();
524
525 // Make sure we invalidate the containing block cache for flows when the contianing block context changes
526 // so that styleDidChange can safely use RenderBlock::locateEnclosingFragmentedFlow()
527 if (oldStyle.position() != m_style.position())
528 adjustFragmentedFlowStateOnContainingBlockChangeIfNeeded();
529
530 styleDidChange(diff, &oldStyle);
531
532 // Text renderers use their parent style. Notify them about the change.
533 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<RenderText>(*this))
534 child.styleDidChange(diff, &oldStyle);
535
536 // FIXME: |this| might be destroyed here. This can currently happen for a RenderTextFragment when
537 // its first-letter block gets an update in RenderTextFragment::styleDidChange. For RenderTextFragment(s),
538 // we will safely bail out with the detachedFromParent flag. We might want to broaden this condition
539 // in the future as we move renderer changes out of layout and into style changes.
540 if (detachedFromParent)
541 return;
542
543 // Now that the layer (if any) has been updated, we need to adjust the diff again,
544 // check whether we should layout now, and decide if we need to repaint.
545 StyleDifference updatedDiff = adjustStyleDifference(diff, contextSensitiveProperties);
546
547 if (diff <= StyleDifference::LayoutPositionedMovementOnly) {
548 if (updatedDiff == StyleDifference::Layout)
549 setNeedsLayoutAndPrefWidthsRecalc();
550 else if (updatedDiff == StyleDifference::LayoutPositionedMovementOnly)
551 setNeedsPositionedMovementLayout(&oldStyle);
552 else if (updatedDiff == StyleDifference::SimplifiedLayoutAndPositionedMovement) {
553 setNeedsPositionedMovementLayout(&oldStyle);
554 setNeedsSimplifiedNormalFlowLayout();
555 } else if (updatedDiff == StyleDifference::SimplifiedLayout)
556 setNeedsSimplifiedNormalFlowLayout();
557 }
558
559 if (!didRepaint && (updatedDiff == StyleDifference::RepaintLayer || shouldRepaintForStyleDifference(updatedDiff))) {
560 // Do a repaint with the new style now, e.g., for example if we go from
561 // not having an outline to having an outline.
562 repaint();
563 }
564}
565
566void RenderElement::didAttachChild(RenderObject& child, RenderObject*)
567{
568 if (is<RenderText>(child))
569 downcast<RenderText>(child).styleDidChange(StyleDifference::Equal, nullptr);
570 // SVG creates renderers for <g display="none">, as SVG requires children of hidden
571 // <g>s to have renderers - at least that's how our implementation works. Consider:
572 // <g display="none"><foreignObject><body style="position: relative">FOO...
573 // - requiresLayer() would return true for the <body>, creating a new RenderLayer
574 // - when the document is painted, both layers are painted. The <body> layer doesn't
575 // know that it's inside a "hidden SVG subtree", and thus paints, even if it shouldn't.
576 // To avoid the problem alltogether, detect early if we're inside a hidden SVG subtree
577 // and stop creating layers at all for these cases - they're not used anyways.
578 if (child.hasLayer() && !layerCreationAllowedForSubtree())
579 downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(child).layer()->removeOnlyThisLayer(RenderLayer::LayerChangeTiming::RenderTreeConstruction);
580}
581
582RenderObject* RenderElement::attachRendererInternal(RenderPtr<RenderObject> child, RenderObject* beforeChild)
583{
584 child->setParent(this);
585
586 if (m_firstChild == beforeChild)
587 m_firstChild = child.get();
588
589 if (beforeChild) {
590 auto* previousSibling = beforeChild->previousSibling();
591 if (previousSibling)
592 previousSibling->setNextSibling(child.get());
593 child->setPreviousSibling(previousSibling);
594 child->setNextSibling(beforeChild);
595 beforeChild->setPreviousSibling(child.get());
596 return child.release();
597 }
598 if (m_lastChild)
599 m_lastChild->setNextSibling(child.get());
600 child->setPreviousSibling(m_lastChild);
601 m_lastChild = child.get();
602 return child.release();
603}
604
605RenderPtr<RenderObject> RenderElement::detachRendererInternal(RenderObject& renderer)
606{
607 auto* parent = renderer.parent();
608 ASSERT(parent);
609 auto* nextSibling = renderer.nextSibling();
610
611 if (renderer.previousSibling())
612 renderer.previousSibling()->setNextSibling(nextSibling);
613 if (nextSibling)
614 nextSibling->setPreviousSibling(renderer.previousSibling());
615
616 if (parent->firstChild() == &renderer)
617 parent->m_firstChild = nextSibling;
618 if (parent->lastChild() == &renderer)
619 parent->m_lastChild = renderer.previousSibling();
620
621 renderer.setPreviousSibling(nullptr);
622 renderer.setNextSibling(nullptr);
623 renderer.setParent(nullptr);
624 return RenderPtr<RenderObject>(&renderer);
625}
626
627static inline RenderBlock* nearestNonAnonymousContainingBlockIncludingSelf(RenderElement* renderer)
628{
629 while (renderer && (!is<RenderBlock>(*renderer) || renderer->isAnonymousBlock()))
630 renderer = renderer->containingBlock();
631 return downcast<RenderBlock>(renderer);
632}
633
634RenderBlock* RenderElement::containingBlockForFixedPosition() const
635{
636 auto* ancestor = parent();
637 while (ancestor && !ancestor->canContainFixedPositionObjects())
638 ancestor = ancestor->parent();
639 return nearestNonAnonymousContainingBlockIncludingSelf(ancestor);
640}
641
642RenderBlock* RenderElement::containingBlockForAbsolutePosition() const
643{
644 if (is<RenderInline>(*this) && style().position() == PositionType::Relative) {
645 // A relatively positioned RenderInline forwards its absolute positioned descendants to
646 // its nearest non-anonymous containing block (to avoid having positioned objects list in RenderInlines).
647 return nearestNonAnonymousContainingBlockIncludingSelf(parent());
648 }
649 auto* ancestor = parent();
650 while (ancestor && !ancestor->canContainAbsolutelyPositionedObjects())
651 ancestor = ancestor->parent();
652 // Make sure we only return non-anonymous RenderBlock as containing block.
653 return nearestNonAnonymousContainingBlockIncludingSelf(ancestor);
654}
655
656static void addLayers(RenderElement& renderer, RenderLayer* parentLayer, RenderElement*& newObject, RenderLayer*& beforeChild)
657{
658 if (renderer.hasLayer()) {
659 if (!beforeChild && newObject) {
660 // We need to figure out the layer that follows newObject. We only do
661 // this the first time we find a child layer, and then we update the
662 // pointer values for newObject and beforeChild used by everyone else.
663 beforeChild = newObject->parent()->findNextLayer(parentLayer, newObject);
664 newObject = nullptr;
665 }
666 parentLayer->addChild(*downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(renderer).layer(), beforeChild);
667 return;
668 }
669
670 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<RenderElement>(renderer))
671 addLayers(child, parentLayer, newObject, beforeChild);
672}
673
674void RenderElement::addLayers(RenderLayer* parentLayer)
675{
676 if (!parentLayer)
677 return;
678
679 RenderElement* renderer = this;
680 RenderLayer* beforeChild = nullptr;
681 WebCore::addLayers(*this, parentLayer, renderer, beforeChild);
682}
683
684void RenderElement::removeLayers(RenderLayer* parentLayer)
685{
686 if (!parentLayer)
687 return;
688
689 if (hasLayer()) {
690 parentLayer->removeChild(*downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this).layer());
691 return;
692 }
693
694 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<RenderElement>(*this))
695 child.removeLayers(parentLayer);
696}
697
698void RenderElement::moveLayers(RenderLayer* oldParent, RenderLayer* newParent)
699{
700 if (!newParent)
701 return;
702
703 if (hasLayer()) {
704 RenderLayer* layer = downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this).layer();
705 ASSERT(oldParent == layer->parent());
706 if (oldParent)
707 oldParent->removeChild(*layer);
708 newParent->addChild(*layer);
709 return;
710 }
711
712 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<RenderElement>(*this))
713 child.moveLayers(oldParent, newParent);
714}
715
716RenderLayer* RenderElement::findNextLayer(RenderLayer* parentLayer, RenderObject* startPoint, bool checkParent)
717{
718 // Error check the parent layer passed in. If it's null, we can't find anything.
719 if (!parentLayer)
720 return nullptr;
721
722 // Step 1: If our layer is a child of the desired parent, then return our layer.
723 RenderLayer* ourLayer = hasLayer() ? downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this).layer() : nullptr;
724 if (ourLayer && ourLayer->parent() == parentLayer)
725 return ourLayer;
726
727 // Step 2: If we don't have a layer, or our layer is the desired parent, then descend
728 // into our siblings trying to find the next layer whose parent is the desired parent.
729 if (!ourLayer || ourLayer == parentLayer) {
730 for (RenderObject* child = startPoint ? startPoint->nextSibling() : firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
731 if (!is<RenderElement>(*child))
732 continue;
733 RenderLayer* nextLayer = downcast<RenderElement>(*child).findNextLayer(parentLayer, nullptr, false);
734 if (nextLayer)
735 return nextLayer;
736 }
737 }
738
739 // Step 3: If our layer is the desired parent layer, then we're finished. We didn't
740 // find anything.
741 if (parentLayer == ourLayer)
742 return nullptr;
743
744 // Step 4: If |checkParent| is set, climb up to our parent and check its siblings that
745 // follow us to see if we can locate a layer.
746 if (checkParent && parent())
747 return parent()->findNextLayer(parentLayer, this, true);
748
749 return nullptr;
750}
751
752bool RenderElement::layerCreationAllowedForSubtree() const
753{
754 RenderElement* parentRenderer = parent();
755 while (parentRenderer) {
756 if (parentRenderer->isSVGHiddenContainer())
757 return false;
758 parentRenderer = parentRenderer->parent();
759 }
760
761 return true;
762}
763
764void RenderElement::propagateStyleToAnonymousChildren(StylePropagationType propagationType)
765{
766 // FIXME: We could save this call when the change only affected non-inherited properties.
767 for (auto& elementChild : childrenOfType<RenderElement>(*this)) {
768 if (!elementChild.isAnonymous() || elementChild.style().styleType() != PseudoId::None)
769 continue;
770
771 if (propagationType == PropagateToBlockChildrenOnly && !is<RenderBlock>(elementChild))
772 continue;
773
774#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
775 if (elementChild.isRenderFullScreen() || elementChild.isRenderFullScreenPlaceholder())
776 continue;
777#endif
778
779 // RenderFragmentedFlows are updated through the RenderView::styleDidChange function.
780 if (is<RenderFragmentedFlow>(elementChild))
781 continue;
782
783 auto newStyle = RenderStyle::createAnonymousStyleWithDisplay(style(), elementChild.style().display());
784 if (style().specifiesColumns()) {
785 if (elementChild.style().specifiesColumns())
786 newStyle.inheritColumnPropertiesFrom(style());
787 if (elementChild.style().columnSpan() == ColumnSpan::All)
788 newStyle.setColumnSpan(ColumnSpan::All);
789 }
790
791 // Preserve the position style of anonymous block continuations as they can have relative or sticky position when
792 // they contain block descendants of relative or sticky positioned inlines.
793 if (elementChild.isInFlowPositioned() && elementChild.isContinuation())
794 newStyle.setPosition(elementChild.style().position());
795
796 updateAnonymousChildStyle(newStyle);
797
798 elementChild.setStyle(WTFMove(newStyle));
799 }
800}

807void RenderElement::invalidateCachedFirstLineStyle()
808{
809 if (!m_hasValidCachedFirstLineStyle)
810 return;
811 m_hasValidCachedFirstLineStyle = false;
812 // Invalidate the subtree as descendant's first line style may depend on ancestor's.
813 for (auto& descendant : descendantsOfType<RenderElement>(*this))
814 descendant.m_hasValidCachedFirstLineStyle = false;
815}
816
817void RenderElement::styleWillChange(StyleDifference diff, const RenderStyle& newStyle)
818{
819 ASSERT(settings().shouldAllowUserInstalledFonts() || newStyle.fontDescription().shouldAllowUserInstalledFonts() == AllowUserInstalledFonts::No);
820
821 auto* oldStyle = hasInitializedStyle() ? &style() : nullptr;
822 if (oldStyle) {
823 // If our z-index changes value or our visibility changes,
824 // we need to dirty our stacking context's z-order list.
825 bool visibilityChanged = m_style.visibility() != newStyle.visibility()
826 || m_style.usedZIndex() != newStyle.usedZIndex()
827 || m_style.hasAutoUsedZIndex() != newStyle.hasAutoUsedZIndex();
828
829 if (visibilityChanged)
830 document().invalidateRenderingDependentRegions();
831
832 if (visibilityChanged) {
833 if (AXObjectCache* cache = document().existingAXObjectCache())
834 cache->childrenChanged(parent(), this);
835 }
836
837 // Keep layer hierarchy visibility bits up to date if visibility changes.
838 if (m_style.visibility() != newStyle.visibility()) {
839 if (RenderLayer* layer = enclosingLayer()) {
840 if (newStyle.visibility() == Visibility::Visible)
841 layer->setHasVisibleContent();
842 else if (layer->hasVisibleContent() && (this == &layer->renderer() || layer->renderer().style().visibility() != Visibility::Visible))
843 layer->dirtyVisibleContentStatus();
844 }
845 }
846
847 auto needsInvalidateEventRegion = [&] {
848 if (m_style.pointerEvents() != newStyle.pointerEvents())
849 return true;
850#if ENABLE(TOUCH_ACTION_REGIONS)
851 if (m_style.effectiveTouchActions() != newStyle.effectiveTouchActions())
852 return true;
853#endif
854 if (m_style.eventListenerRegionTypes() != newStyle.eventListenerRegionTypes())
855 return true;
856#if ENABLE(EDITABLE_REGION)
857 bool wasEditable = m_style.userModify() != UserModify::ReadOnly;
858 bool isEditable = newStyle.userModify() != UserModify::ReadOnly;
859 if (wasEditable != isEditable)
860 return page().shouldBuildEditableRegion();
861#endif
862 return false;
863 };
864
865 if (needsInvalidateEventRegion()) {
866 // Usually the event region gets updated as a result of paint invalidation. Here we need to request an update explicitly.
867 if (auto* layer = enclosingLayer())
868 layer->invalidateEventRegion(RenderLayer::EventRegionInvalidationReason::Style);
869 }
870
871 if (isFloating() && m_style.floating() != newStyle.floating()) {
872 // For changes in float styles, we need to conceivably remove ourselves
873 // from the floating objects list.
874 downcast<RenderBox>(*this).removeFloatingOrPositionedChildFromBlockLists();
875 } else if (isOutOfFlowPositioned() && m_style.position() != newStyle.position()) {
876 // For changes in positioning styles, we need to conceivably remove ourselves
877 // from the positioned objects list.
878 downcast<RenderBox>(*this).removeFloatingOrPositionedChildFromBlockLists();
879 }
880
881 // reset style flags
882 if (diff == StyleDifference::Layout || diff == StyleDifference::LayoutPositionedMovementOnly) {
883 setFloating(false);
884 clearPositionedState();
885 }
886
887 if (newStyle.hasPseudoStyle(PseudoId::FirstLine) || oldStyle->hasPseudoStyle(PseudoId::FirstLine))
888 invalidateCachedFirstLineStyle();
889
890 setHorizontalWritingMode(true);
891 setHasVisibleBoxDecorations(false);
892 setHasOverflowClip(false);
893 setHasTransformRelatedProperty(false);
894 setHasReflection(false);
895 }
896
897 bool hadOutline = oldStyle && oldStyle->hasOutline();
898 bool hasOutline = newStyle.hasOutline();
899 if (hadOutline != hasOutline) {
900 if (hasOutline)
901 view().incrementRendersWithOutline();
902 else
903 view().decrementRendersWithOutline();
904 }
905
906 bool newStyleSlowScroll = false;
907 if (newStyle.hasFixedBackgroundImage() && !settings().fixedBackgroundsPaintRelativeToDocument()) {
908 newStyleSlowScroll = true;
909 bool drawsRootBackground = isDocumentElementRenderer() || (isBody() && !rendererHasBackground(document().documentElement()->renderer()));
910 if (drawsRootBackground && newStyle.hasEntirelyFixedBackground() && view().compositor().supportsFixedRootBackgroundCompositing())
911 newStyleSlowScroll = false;
912 }
913
914 if (view().frameView().hasSlowRepaintObject(*this)) {
915 if (!newStyleSlowScroll)
916 view().frameView().removeSlowRepaintObject(*this);
917 } else if (newStyleSlowScroll)
918 view().frameView().addSlowRepaintObject(*this);
919
920 if (isDocumentElementRenderer() || isBody())
921 view().frameView().updateExtendBackgroundIfNecessary();
922}
923
924#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
925static bool areNonIdenticalCursorListsEqual(const RenderStyle* a, const RenderStyle* b)
926{
927 ASSERT(a->cursors() != b->cursors());
928 return a->cursors() && b->cursors() && *a->cursors() == *b->cursors();
929}
930
931static inline bool areCursorsEqual(const RenderStyle* a, const RenderStyle* b)
932{
933 return a->cursor() == b->cursor() && (a->cursors() == b->cursors() || areNonIdenticalCursorListsEqual(a, b));
934}
935#endif
936
937void RenderElement::styleDidChange(StyleDifference diff, const RenderStyle* oldStyle)
938{
939 updateFillImages(oldStyle ? &oldStyle->backgroundLayers() : nullptr, m_style.backgroundLayers());
940 updateFillImages(oldStyle ? &oldStyle->maskLayers() : nullptr, m_style.maskLayers());
941 updateImage(oldStyle ? oldStyle->borderImage().image() : nullptr, m_style.borderImage().image());
942 updateImage(oldStyle ? oldStyle->maskBoxImage().image() : nullptr, m_style.maskBoxImage().image());
943 updateShapeImage(oldStyle ? oldStyle->shapeOutside() : nullptr, m_style.shapeOutside());
944
945 SVGRenderSupport::styleChanged(*this, oldStyle);
946
947 if (!m_parent)
948 return;
949
950 if (diff == StyleDifference::Layout || diff == StyleDifference::SimplifiedLayout) {
951 RenderCounter::rendererStyleChanged(*this, oldStyle, m_style);
952
953 // If the object already needs layout, then setNeedsLayout won't do
954 // any work. But if the containing block has changed, then we may need
955 // to mark the new containing blocks for layout. The change that can
956 // directly affect the containing block of this object is a change to
957 // the position style.
958 if (needsLayout() && oldStyle && oldStyle->position() != m_style.position())
959 markContainingBlocksForLayout();
960
961 if (diff == StyleDifference::Layout)
962 setNeedsLayoutAndPrefWidthsRecalc();
963 else
964 setNeedsSimplifiedNormalFlowLayout();
965 } else if (diff == StyleDifference::SimplifiedLayoutAndPositionedMovement) {
966 setNeedsPositionedMovementLayout(oldStyle);
967 setNeedsSimplifiedNormalFlowLayout();
968 } else if (diff == StyleDifference::LayoutPositionedMovementOnly)
969 setNeedsPositionedMovementLayout(oldStyle);
970
971 // Don't check for repaint here; we need to wait until the layer has been
972 // updated by subclasses before we know if we have to repaint (in setStyle()).
973
974#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
975 if (oldStyle && !areCursorsEqual(oldStyle, &style()))
976 frame().eventHandler().scheduleCursorUpdate();
977#endif
978
979 bool hadOutlineAuto = oldStyle && oldStyle->outlineStyleIsAuto() == OutlineIsAuto::On;
980 bool hasOutlineAuto = outlineStyleForRepaint().outlineStyleIsAuto() == OutlineIsAuto::On;
981 if (hasOutlineAuto != hadOutlineAuto) {
982 updateOutlineAutoAncestor(hasOutlineAuto);
983 issueRepaintForOutlineAuto(hasOutlineAuto ? outlineStyleForRepaint().outlineSize() : oldStyle->outlineSize());
984 }
985}
986
987void RenderElement::insertedIntoTree(IsInternalMove isInternalMove)
988{
989 // Keep our layer hierarchy updated. Optimize for the common case where we don't have any children
990 // and don't have a layer attached to ourselves.
991 RenderLayer* layer = nullptr;
992 if (firstChild() || hasLayer()) {
993 layer = parent()->enclosingLayer();
994 addLayers(layer);
995 }
996
997 // If |this| is visible but this object was not, tell the layer it has some visible content
998 // that needs to be drawn and layer visibility optimization can't be used
999 if (parent()->style().visibility() != Visibility::Visible && style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible && !hasLayer()) {
1000 if (!layer)
1001 layer = parent()->enclosingLayer();
1002 if (layer)
1003 layer->dirtyVisibleContentStatus();
1004 }
1005
1006 RenderObject::insertedIntoTree(isInternalMove);
1007}
1008
1009void RenderElement::willBeRemovedFromTree(IsInternalMove isInternalMove)
1010{
1011 // If we remove a visible child from an invisible parent, we don't know the layer visibility any more.
1012 RenderLayer* layer = nullptr;
1013 if (parent()->style().visibility() != Visibility::Visible && style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible && !hasLayer()) {
1014 if ((layer = parent()->enclosingLayer()))
1015 layer->dirtyVisibleContentStatus();
1016 }
1017 // Keep our layer hierarchy updated.
1018 if (firstChild() || hasLayer()) {
1019 if (!layer)
1020 layer = parent()->enclosingLayer();
1021 removeLayers(layer);
1022 }
1023
1024 if (isOutOfFlowPositioned() && parent()->childrenInline())
1025 parent()->dirtyLinesFromChangedChild(*this);
1026
1027 RenderObject::willBeRemovedFromTree(isInternalMove);
1028}

1030inline void RenderElement::clearSubtreeLayoutRootIfNeeded() const
1031{
1032 if (renderTreeBeingDestroyed())
1033 return;
1034
1035 if (view().frameView().layoutContext().subtreeLayoutRoot() != this)
1036 return;
1037
1038 // Normally when a renderer is detached from the tree, the appropriate dirty bits get set
1039 // which ensures that this renderer is no longer the layout root.
1040 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1041
1042 // This indicates a failure to layout the child, which is why
1043 // the layout root is still set to |this|. Make sure to clear it
1044 // since we are getting destroyed.
1045 view().frameView().layoutContext().clearSubtreeLayoutRoot();
1046}
1047
1048void RenderElement::willBeDestroyed()
1049{
1050#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1051 if (!renderTreeBeingDestroyed() && element())
1052 document().contentChangeObserver().rendererWillBeDestroyed(*element());
1053#endif
1054 if (m_style.hasFixedBackgroundImage() && !settings().fixedBackgroundsPaintRelativeToDocument())
1055 view().frameView().removeSlowRepaintObject(*this);
1056
1057 unregisterForVisibleInViewportCallback();
1058
1059 if (hasCounterNodeMap())
1060 RenderCounter::destroyCounterNodes(*this);
1061
1062 if (style().hasOutline())
1063 view().decrementRendersWithOutline();
1064
1065 RenderObject::willBeDestroyed();
1066
1067 clearSubtreeLayoutRootIfNeeded();
1068
1069 if (hasInitializedStyle()) {
1070 for (auto* bgLayer = &m_style.backgroundLayers(); bgLayer; bgLayer = bgLayer->next()) {
1071 if (auto* backgroundImage = bgLayer->image())
1072 backgroundImage->removeClient(*this);
1073 }
1074 for (auto* maskLayer = &m_style.maskLayers(); maskLayer; maskLayer = maskLayer->next()) {
1075 if (auto* maskImage = maskLayer->image())
1076 maskImage->removeClient(*this);
1077 }
1078 if (auto* borderImage = m_style.borderImage().image())
1079 borderImage->removeClient(*this);
1080 if (auto* maskBoxImage = m_style.maskBoxImage().image())
1081 maskBoxImage->removeClient(*this);
1082 if (auto shapeValue = m_style.shapeOutside()) {
1083 if (auto shapeImage = shapeValue->image())
1084 shapeImage->removeClient(*this);
1085 }
1086 }
1087 if (m_hasPausedImageAnimations)
1088 view().removeRendererWithPausedImageAnimations(*this);
1089}

1126static inline void paintPhase(RenderElement& element, PaintPhase phase, PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& childPoint)
1127{
1128 paintInfo.phase = phase;
1129 element.paint(paintInfo, childPoint);
1130}
1131
1132void RenderElement::paintAsInlineBlock(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& childPoint)
1133{
1134 // Paint all phases atomically, as though the element established its own stacking context.
1135 // (See Appendix E.2, section 6.4 on inline block/table/replaced elements in the CSS2.1 specification.)
1136 // This is also used by other elements (e.g. flex items and grid items).
1137 PaintPhase paintPhaseToUse = isExcludedAndPlacedInBorder() ? paintInfo.phase : PaintPhase::Foreground;
1138 if (paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::Selection || paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::EventRegion)
1139 paint(paintInfo, childPoint);
1140 else if (paintInfo.phase == paintPhaseToUse) {
1141 paintPhase(*this, PaintPhase::BlockBackground, paintInfo, childPoint);
1142 paintPhase(*this, PaintPhase::ChildBlockBackgrounds, paintInfo, childPoint);
1143 paintPhase(*this, PaintPhase::Float, paintInfo, childPoint);
1144 paintPhase(*this, PaintPhase::Foreground, paintInfo, childPoint);
1145 paintPhase(*this, PaintPhase::Outline, paintInfo, childPoint);
1146
1147 // Reset |paintInfo| to the original phase.
1148 paintInfo.phase = paintPhaseToUse;
1149 }
1150}
1151
1152void RenderElement::layout()
1153{
1154 StackStats::LayoutCheckPoint layoutCheckPoint;
1155 ASSERT(needsLayout());
1156 for (auto* child = firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
1157 if (child->needsLayout())
1158 downcast<RenderElement>(*child).layout();
1159 ASSERT(!child->needsLayout());
1160 }
1161 clearNeedsLayout();
1162}
1163
1164static bool mustRepaintFillLayers(const RenderElement& renderer, const FillLayer& layer)
1165{
1166 // Nobody will use multiple layers without wanting fancy positioning.
1167 if (layer.next())
1168 return true;
1169
1170 // Make sure we have a valid image.
1171 auto* image = layer.image();
1172 if (!image || !image->canRender(&renderer, renderer.style().effectiveZoom()))
1173 return false;
1174
1175 if (!layer.xPosition().isZero() || !layer.yPosition().isZero())
1176 return true;
1177
1178 auto sizeType = layer.sizeType();
1179
1180 if (sizeType == FillSizeType::Contain || sizeType == FillSizeType::Cover)
1181 return true;
1182
1183 if (sizeType == FillSizeType::Size) {
1184 auto size = layer.sizeLength();
1185 if (size.width.isPercentOrCalculated() || size.height.isPercentOrCalculated())
1186 return true;
1187 // If the image has neither an intrinsic width nor an intrinsic height, its size is determined as for 'contain'.
1188 if ((size.width.isAuto() || size.height.isAuto()) && image->isGeneratedImage())
1189 return true;
1190 } else if (image->usesImageContainerSize())
1191 return true;
1192
1193 return false;
1194}
1195
1196static bool mustRepaintBackgroundOrBorder(const RenderElement& renderer)
1197{
1198 if (renderer.hasMask() && mustRepaintFillLayers(renderer, renderer.style().maskLayers()))
1199 return true;
1200
1201 // If we don't have a background/border/mask, then nothing to do.
1202 if (!renderer.hasVisibleBoxDecorations())
1203 return false;
1204
1205 if (mustRepaintFillLayers(renderer, renderer.style().backgroundLayers()))
1206 return true;
1207
1208 // Our fill layers are ok. Let's check border.
1209 if (renderer.style().hasBorder() && renderer.borderImageIsLoadedAndCanBeRendered())
1210 return true;
1211
1212 return false;
1213}
1214
1215bool RenderElement::repaintAfterLayoutIfNeeded(const RenderLayerModelObject* repaintContainer, const LayoutRect& oldBounds, const LayoutRect& oldOutlineBox, const LayoutRect* newBoundsPtr, const LayoutRect* newOutlineBoxRectPtr)
1216{
1217 if (view().printing())
1218 return false; // Don't repaint if we're printing.
1219
1220 // This ASSERT fails due to animations. See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=37048
1221 // ASSERT(!newBoundsPtr || *newBoundsPtr == clippedOverflowRectForRepaint(repaintContainer));
1222 LayoutRect newBounds = newBoundsPtr ? *newBoundsPtr : clippedOverflowRectForRepaint(repaintContainer);
1223 LayoutRect newOutlineBox;
1224
1225 bool fullRepaint = selfNeedsLayout();
1226 // Presumably a background or a border exists if border-fit:lines was specified.
1227 if (!fullRepaint && style().borderFit() == BorderFit::Lines)
1228 fullRepaint = true;
1229 if (!fullRepaint) {
1230 // This ASSERT fails due to animations. See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=37048
1231 // ASSERT(!newOutlineBoxRectPtr || *newOutlineBoxRectPtr == outlineBoundsForRepaint(repaintContainer));
1232 newOutlineBox = newOutlineBoxRectPtr ? *newOutlineBoxRectPtr : outlineBoundsForRepaint(repaintContainer);
1233 fullRepaint = (newOutlineBox.location() != oldOutlineBox.location() || (mustRepaintBackgroundOrBorder(*this) && (newBounds != oldBounds || newOutlineBox != oldOutlineBox)));
1234 }
1235
1236 if (!repaintContainer)
1237 repaintContainer = &view();
1238
1239 if (fullRepaint) {
1240 repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, oldBounds);
1241 if (newBounds != oldBounds)
1242 repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, newBounds);
1243 return true;
1244 }
1245
1246 if (newBounds == oldBounds && newOutlineBox == oldOutlineBox)
1247 return false;
1248
1249 LayoutUnit deltaLeft = newBounds.x() - oldBounds.x();
1250 if (deltaLeft > 0)
1251 repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, LayoutRect(oldBounds.x(), oldBounds.y(), deltaLeft, oldBounds.height()));
1252 else if (deltaLeft < 0)
1253 repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, LayoutRect(newBounds.x(), newBounds.y(), -deltaLeft, newBounds.height()));
1254
1255 LayoutUnit deltaRight = newBounds.maxX() - oldBounds.maxX();
1256 if (deltaRight > 0)
1257 repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, LayoutRect(oldBounds.maxX(), newBounds.y(), deltaRight, newBounds.height()));
1258 else if (deltaRight < 0)
1259 repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, LayoutRect(newBounds.maxX(), oldBounds.y(), -deltaRight, oldBounds.height()));
1260
1261 LayoutUnit deltaTop = newBounds.y() - oldBounds.y();
1262 if (deltaTop > 0)
1263 repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, LayoutRect(oldBounds.x(), oldBounds.y(), oldBounds.width(), deltaTop));
1264 else if (deltaTop < 0)
1265 repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, LayoutRect(newBounds.x(), newBounds.y(), newBounds.width(), -deltaTop));
1266
1267 LayoutUnit deltaBottom = newBounds.maxY() - oldBounds.maxY();
1268 if (deltaBottom > 0)
1269 repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, LayoutRect(newBounds.x(), oldBounds.maxY(), newBounds.width(), deltaBottom));
1270 else if (deltaBottom < 0)
1271 repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, LayoutRect(oldBounds.x(), newBounds.maxY(), oldBounds.width(), -deltaBottom));
1272
1273 if (newOutlineBox == oldOutlineBox)
1274 return false;
1275
1276 // We didn't move, but we did change size. Invalidate the delta, which will consist of possibly
1277 // two rectangles (but typically only one).
1278 const RenderStyle& outlineStyle = outlineStyleForRepaint();
1279 LayoutUnit outlineWidth { outlineStyle.outlineSize() };
1280 auto insetShadowExtent = style().boxShadowInsetExtent();
1281 LayoutUnit width = absoluteValue(newOutlineBox.width() - oldOutlineBox.width());
1282 if (width) {
1283 LayoutUnit shadowLeft;
1284 LayoutUnit shadowRight;
1285 style().getBoxShadowHorizontalExtent(shadowLeft, shadowRight);
1286 LayoutUnit borderRight = is<RenderBox>(*this) ? downcast<RenderBox>(*this).borderRight() : 0_lu;
1287 LayoutUnit boxWidth = is<RenderBox>(*this) ? downcast<RenderBox>(*this).width() : 0_lu;
1288 LayoutUnit minInsetRightShadowExtent = std::min<LayoutUnit>(-insetShadowExtent.right(), std::min(newBounds.width(), oldBounds.width()));
1289 LayoutUnit borderWidth = std::max(borderRight, std::max(valueForLength(style().borderTopRightRadius().width, boxWidth), valueForLength(style().borderBottomRightRadius().width, boxWidth)));
1290 LayoutUnit decorationsWidth = std::max(LayoutUnit(-outlineStyle.outlineOffset()), borderWidth + minInsetRightShadowExtent) + std::max(outlineWidth, shadowRight);
1291 LayoutRect rightRect(newOutlineBox.x() + std::min(newOutlineBox.width(), oldOutlineBox.width()) - decorationsWidth,
1292 newOutlineBox.y(),
1293 width + decorationsWidth,
1294 std::max(newOutlineBox.height(), oldOutlineBox.height()));
1295 LayoutUnit right = std::min(newBounds.maxX(), oldBounds.maxX());
1296 if (rightRect.x() < right) {
1297 rightRect.setWidth(std::min(rightRect.width(), right - rightRect.x()));
1298 repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, rightRect);
1299 }
1300 }
1301 LayoutUnit height = absoluteValue(newOutlineBox.height() - oldOutlineBox.height());
1302 if (height) {
1303 LayoutUnit shadowTop;
1304 LayoutUnit shadowBottom;
1305 style().getBoxShadowVerticalExtent(shadowTop, shadowBottom);
1306 LayoutUnit borderBottom = is<RenderBox>(*this) ? downcast<RenderBox>(*this).borderBottom() : 0_lu;
1307 LayoutUnit boxHeight = is<RenderBox>(*this) ? downcast<RenderBox>(*this).height() : 0_lu;
1308 LayoutUnit minInsetBottomShadowExtent = std::min<LayoutUnit>(-insetShadowExtent.bottom(), std::min(newBounds.height(), oldBounds.height()));
1309 LayoutUnit borderHeight = std::max(borderBottom, std::max(valueForLength(style().borderBottomLeftRadius().height, boxHeight),
1310 valueForLength(style().borderBottomRightRadius().height, boxHeight)));
1311 LayoutUnit decorationsHeight = std::max(LayoutUnit(-outlineStyle.outlineOffset()), borderHeight + minInsetBottomShadowExtent) + std::max(outlineWidth, shadowBottom);
1312 LayoutRect bottomRect(newOutlineBox.x(),
1313 std::min(newOutlineBox.maxY(), oldOutlineBox.maxY()) - decorationsHeight,
1314 std::max(newOutlineBox.width(), oldOutlineBox.width()),
1315 height + decorationsHeight);
1316 LayoutUnit bottom = std::min(newBounds.maxY(), oldBounds.maxY());
1317 if (bottomRect.y() < bottom) {
1318 bottomRect.setHeight(std::min(bottomRect.height(), bottom - bottomRect.y()));
1319 repaintUsingContainer(repaintContainer, bottomRect);
1320 }
1321 }
1322 return false;
1323}

1332
1333bool RenderElement::mayCauseRepaintInsideViewport(const IntRect* optionalViewportRect) const
1334{
1335 auto& frameView = view().frameView();
1336 if (frameView.isOffscreen())
1337 return false;
1338
1339 if (!hasOverflowClip()) {
1340 // FIXME: Computing the overflow rect is expensive if any descendant has
1341 // its own self-painting layer. As a result, we prefer to abort early in
1342 // this case and assume it may cause us to repaint inside the viewport.
1343 if (!hasLayer() || downcast<RenderLayerModelObject>(*this).layer()->firstChild())
1344 return true;
1345 }
1346
1347 // Compute viewport rect if it was not provided.
1348 const IntRect& visibleRect = optionalViewportRect ? *optionalViewportRect : frameView.windowToContents(frameView.windowClipRect());
1349 return visibleRect.intersects(enclosingIntRect(absoluteClippedOverflowRectForRepaint()));
1350}

1352bool RenderElement::isVisibleIgnoringGeometry() const
1353{
1354 if (document().activeDOMObjectsAreSuspended())
1355 return false;
1356 if (style().visibility() != Visibility::Visible)
1357 return false;
1358 if (view().frameView().isOffscreen())
1359 return false;
1360
1361 return true;
1362}
1363
1364bool RenderElement::isVisibleInDocumentRect(const IntRect& documentRect) const
1365{
1366 if (!isVisibleIgnoringGeometry())
1367 return false;
1368
1369 // Use background rect if we are the root or if we are the body and the background is propagated to the root.
1370 // FIXME: This is overly conservative as the image may not be a background-image, in which case it will not
1371 // be propagated to the root. At this point, we unfortunately don't have access to the image anymore so we
1372 // can no longer check if it is a background image.
1373 bool backgroundIsPaintedByRoot = isDocumentElementRenderer();
1374 if (isBody()) {
1375 auto& rootRenderer = *parent(); // If <body> has a renderer then <html> does too.
1376 ASSERT(rootRenderer.isDocumentElementRenderer());
1377 ASSERT(is<HTMLHtmlElement>(rootRenderer.element()));
1378 // FIXME: Should share body background propagation code.
1379 backgroundIsPaintedByRoot = !rootRenderer.hasBackground();
1380 }
1381
1382 LayoutRect backgroundPaintingRect = backgroundIsPaintedByRoot ? view().backgroundRect() : absoluteClippedOverflowRectForRepaint();
1383 if (!documentRect.intersects(enclosingIntRect(backgroundPaintingRect)))
1384 return false;
1385
1386 return true;
1387}

1427VisibleInViewportState RenderElement::imageFrameAvailable(CachedImage& image, ImageAnimatingState animatingState, const IntRect* changeRect)
1428{
1429 bool isVisible = isVisibleInViewport();
1430
1431 if (!isVisible && animatingState == ImageAnimatingState::Yes)
1432 view().addRendererWithPausedImageAnimations(*this, image);
1433
1434 // Static images should repaint even if they are outside the viewport rectangle
1435 // because they should be inside the TileCoverageRect.
1436 if (isVisible || animatingState == ImageAnimatingState::No)
1437 imageChanged(&image, changeRect);
1438
1439 if (element() && image.image()->isBitmapImage())
1440 element()->dispatchWebKitImageReadyEventForTesting();
1441
1442 return isVisible ? VisibleInViewportState::Yes : VisibleInViewportState::No;
1443}

1470bool RenderElement::repaintForPausedImageAnimationsIfNeeded(const IntRect& visibleRect, CachedImage& cachedImage)
1471{
1472 ASSERT(m_hasPausedImageAnimations);
1473 if (!isVisibleInDocumentRect(visibleRect))
1474 return false;
1475
1476 repaint();
1477
1478 if (auto* image = cachedImage.image()) {
1479 if (is<SVGImage>(image))
1480 downcast<SVGImage>(image)->scheduleStartAnimation();
1481 else
1482 image->startAnimation();
1483 }
1484
1485 // For directly-composited animated GIFs it does not suffice to call repaint() to resume animation. We need to mark the image as changed.
1486 if (is<RenderBoxModelObject>(*this))
1487 downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(*this).contentChanged(ImageChanged);
1488
1489 return true;
1490}

1492const RenderStyle* RenderElement::getCachedPseudoStyle(PseudoId pseudo, const RenderStyle* parentStyle) const
1493{
1494 if (pseudo < PseudoId::FirstInternalPseudoId && !style().hasPseudoStyle(pseudo))
1495 return nullptr;
1496
1497 RenderStyle* cachedStyle = style().getCachedPseudoStyle(pseudo);
1498 if (cachedStyle)
1499 return cachedStyle;
1500
1501 std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> result = getUncachedPseudoStyle({ pseudo }, parentStyle);
1502 if (result)
1503 return const_cast<RenderStyle&>(m_style).addCachedPseudoStyle(WTFMove(result));
1504 return nullptr;
1505}
1506
1507std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> RenderElement::getUncachedPseudoStyle(const Style::PseudoElementRequest& pseudoElementRequest, const RenderStyle* parentStyle, const RenderStyle* ownStyle) const
1508{
1509 if (pseudoElementRequest.pseudoId < PseudoId::FirstInternalPseudoId && !ownStyle && !style().hasPseudoStyle(pseudoElementRequest.pseudoId))
1510 return nullptr;
1511
1512 if (!parentStyle) {
1513 ASSERT(!ownStyle);
1514 parentStyle = &style();
1515 }
1516
1517 if (isAnonymous())
1518 return nullptr;
1519
1520 auto& styleResolver = element()->styleResolver();
1521
1522 std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> style = styleResolver.pseudoStyleForElement(*element(), pseudoElementRequest, *parentStyle);
1523
1524 if (style)
1525 Style::loadPendingResources(*style, document(), element());
1526
1527 return style;
1528}
1529
1530Color RenderElement::selectionColor(CSSPropertyID colorProperty) const
1531{
1532 // If the element is unselectable, or we are only painting the selection,
1533 // don't override the foreground color with the selection foreground color.
1534 if (style().userSelect() == UserSelect::None
1535 || (view().frameView().paintBehavior().containsAny({ PaintBehavior::SelectionOnly, PaintBehavior::SelectionAndBackgroundsOnly })))
1536 return Color();
1537
1538 if (std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> pseudoStyle = selectionPseudoStyle()) {
1539 Color color = pseudoStyle->visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(colorProperty);
1540 if (!color.isValid())
1541 color = pseudoStyle->visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyColor);
1542 return color;
1543 }
1544
1545 if (frame().selection().isFocusedAndActive())
1546 return theme().activeSelectionForegroundColor(styleColorOptions());
1547 return theme().inactiveSelectionForegroundColor(styleColorOptions());
1548}
1549
1550std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> RenderElement::selectionPseudoStyle() const
1551{
1552 if (isAnonymous())
1553 return nullptr;
1554
1555 if (auto selectionStyle = getUncachedPseudoStyle({ PseudoId::Selection })) {
1556 // We intentionally return the pseudo selection style here if it exists before ascending to
1557 // the shadow host element. This allows us to apply selection pseudo styles in user agent
1558 // shadow roots, instead of always deferring to the shadow host's selection pseudo style.
1559 return selectionStyle;
1560 }
1561
1562 if (auto root = makeRefPtr(element()->containingShadowRoot())) {
1563 if (root->mode() == ShadowRootMode::UserAgent) {
1564 auto currentElement = makeRefPtr(element()->shadowHost());
1565 // When an element has display: contents, this element doesn't have a renderer
1566 // and its children will render as children of the parent element.
1567 while (currentElement && currentElement->hasDisplayContents())
1568 currentElement = currentElement->parentElement();
1569 if (currentElement && currentElement->renderer())
1570 return currentElement->renderer()->getUncachedPseudoStyle({ PseudoId::Selection });
1571 }
1572 }
1573
1574 return nullptr;
1575}

1578{
1579 return selectionColor(CSSPropertyWebkitTextFillColor);
1580}
1581
1582Color RenderElement::selectionEmphasisMarkColor() const

1584 return selectionColor(CSSPropertyWebkitTextEmphasisColor);

1586
1587Color RenderElement::selectionBackgroundColor() const
1588{
1589 if (style().userSelect() == UserSelect::None)
1590 return Color();
1591
1592 if (frame().selection().shouldShowBlockCursor() && frame().selection().isCaret())
1593 return theme().transformSelectionBackgroundColor(style().visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyColor), styleColorOptions());
1594
1595 std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> pseudoStyle = selectionPseudoStyle();
1596 if (pseudoStyle && pseudoStyle->visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor).isValid())
1597 return theme().transformSelectionBackgroundColor(pseudoStyle->visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor), styleColorOptions());
1598
1599 if (frame().selection().isFocusedAndActive())
1600 return theme().activeSelectionBackgroundColor(styleColorOptions());
1601 return theme().inactiveSelectionBackgroundColor(styleColorOptions());
1602}
1603
1604bool RenderElement::getLeadingCorner(FloatPoint& point, bool& insideFixed) const
1605{
1606 if (!isInline() || isReplaced()) {
1607 point = localToAbsolute(FloatPoint(), UseTransforms, &insideFixed);
1608 return true;
1609 }
1610
1611 // find the next text/image child, to get a position
1612 const RenderObject* o = this;
1613 while (o) {
1614 const RenderObject* p = o;
1615 if (RenderObject* child = o->firstChildSlow())
1616 o = child;
1617 else if (o->nextSibling())
1618 o = o->nextSibling();
1619 else {
1620 RenderObject* next = 0;
1621 while (!next && o->parent()) {
1622 o = o->parent();
1623 next = o->nextSibling();
1624 }
1625 o = next;
1626
1627 if (!o)
1628 break;
1629 }
1630 ASSERT(o);
1631
1632 if (!o->isInline() || o->isReplaced()) {
1633 point = o->localToAbsolute(FloatPoint(), UseTransforms, &insideFixed);
1634 return true;
1635 }
1636
1637 if (p->node() && p->node() == element() && is<RenderText>(*o) && !LayoutIntegration::firstTextRunFor(downcast<RenderText>(*o))) {
1638 // do nothing - skip unrendered whitespace that is a child or next sibling of the anchor
1639 } else if (is<RenderText>(*o) || o->isReplaced()) {
1640 point = FloatPoint();
1641 if (is<RenderText>(*o)) {
1642 auto& textRenderer = downcast<RenderText>(*o);
1643 if (auto run = LayoutIntegration::firstTextRunFor(textRenderer))
1644 point.move(textRenderer.linesBoundingBox().x(), run.line()->top());
1645 } else if (is<RenderBox>(*o))
1646 point.moveBy(downcast<RenderBox>(*o).location());
1647 point = o->container()->localToAbsolute(point, UseTransforms, &insideFixed);
1648 return true;
1649 }
1650 }
1651
1652 // If the target doesn't have any children or siblings that could be used to calculate the scroll position, we must be
1653 // at the end of the document. Scroll to the bottom. FIXME: who said anything about scrolling?
1654 if (!o && document().view()) {
1655 point = FloatPoint(0, document().view()->contentsHeight());
1656 return true;
1657 }
1658 return false;
1659}
1660
1661bool RenderElement::getTrailingCorner(FloatPoint& point, bool& insideFixed) const
1662{
1663 if (!isInline() || isReplaced()) {
1664 point = localToAbsolute(LayoutPoint(downcast<RenderBox>(*this).size()), UseTransforms, &insideFixed);
1665 return true;
1666 }
1667
1668 // find the last text/image child, to get a position
1669 const RenderObject* o = this;
1670 while (o) {
1671 if (RenderObject* child = o->lastChildSlow())
1672 o = child;
1673 else if (o->previousSibling())
1674 o = o->previousSibling();
1675 else {
1676 RenderObject* prev = 0;
1677 while (!prev) {
1678 o = o->parent();
1679 if (!o)
1680 return false;
1681 prev = o->previousSibling();
1682 }
1683 o = prev;
1684 }
1685 ASSERT(o);
1686 if (is<RenderText>(*o) || o->isReplaced()) {
1687 point = FloatPoint();
1688 if (is<RenderText>(*o)) {
1689 LayoutRect linesBox = downcast<RenderText>(*o).linesBoundingBox();
1690 if (!linesBox.maxX() && !linesBox.maxY())
1691 continue;
1692 point.moveBy(linesBox.maxXMaxYCorner());
1693 } else
1694 point.moveBy(downcast<RenderBox>(*o).frameRect().maxXMaxYCorner());
1695 point = o->container()->localToAbsolute(point, UseTransforms, &insideFixed);
1696 return true;
1697 }
1698 }
1699 return true;
1700}
1701
1702LayoutRect RenderElement::absoluteAnchorRect(bool* insideFixed) const
1703{
1704 FloatPoint leading, trailing;
1705 bool leadingInFixed = false;
1706 bool trailingInFixed = false;
1707 getLeadingCorner(leading, leadingInFixed);
1708 getTrailingCorner(trailing, trailingInFixed);
1709
1710 FloatPoint upperLeft = leading;
1711 FloatPoint lowerRight = trailing;
1712
1713 // Vertical writing modes might mean the leading point is not in the top left
1714 if (!isInline() || isReplaced()) {
1715 upperLeft = FloatPoint(std::min(leading.x(), trailing.x()), std::min(leading.y(), trailing.y()));
1716 lowerRight = FloatPoint(std::max(leading.x(), trailing.x()), std::max(leading.y(), trailing.y()));
1717 } // Otherwise, it's not obvious what to do.
1718
1719 if (insideFixed) {
1720 // For now, just look at the leading corner. Handling one inside fixed and one not would be tricky.
1721 *insideFixed = leadingInFixed;
1722 }
1723
1724 return enclosingLayoutRect(FloatRect(upperLeft, lowerRight.expandedTo(upperLeft) - upperLeft));
1725}
1726
1727LayoutRect RenderElement::absoluteAnchorRectWithScrollMargin(bool* insideFixed) const
1728{
1729 return absoluteAnchorRect(insideFixed);
1730}
1731
1732const RenderElement* RenderElement::enclosingRendererWithTextDecoration(OptionSet<TextDecoration> textDecoration, bool firstLine) const
1733{
1734 const RenderElement* current = this;
1735 do {
1736 if (current->isRenderBlock())
1737 return current;
1738 if (!current->isRenderInline() || current->isRubyText())
1739 return nullptr;
1740
1741 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = firstLine ? current->firstLineStyle() : current->style();
1742 if (styleToUse.textDecoration() & textDecoration)
1743 return current;
1744 current = current->parent();
1745 } while (current && (!current->element() || (!is<HTMLAnchorElement>(*current->element()) && !current->element()->hasTagName(HTMLNames::fontTag))));
1746
1747 return current;
1748}
1749
1750void RenderElement::drawLineForBoxSide(GraphicsContext& graphicsContext, const FloatRect& rect, BoxSide side, Color color, BorderStyle borderStyle, float adjacentWidth1, float adjacentWidth2, bool antialias) const
1751{
1752 auto drawBorderRect = [&graphicsContext] (const FloatRect& rect)
1753 {
1754 if (rect.isEmpty())
1755 return;
1756 graphicsContext.drawRect(rect);
1757 };
1758
1759 auto drawLineFor = [this, &graphicsContext, color, antialias] (const FloatRect& rect, BoxSide side, BorderStyle borderStyle, const FloatSize& adjacent)
1760 {
1761 if (rect.isEmpty())
1762 return;
1763 drawLineForBoxSide(graphicsContext, rect, side, color, borderStyle, adjacent.width(), adjacent.height(), antialias);
1764 };
1765
1766 float x1 = rect.x();
1767 float x2 = rect.maxX();
1768 float y1 = rect.y();
1769 float y2 = rect.maxY();
1770 float thickness;
1771 float length;
1772 if (side == BoxSide::Top || side == BoxSide::Bottom) {
1773 thickness = y2 - y1;
1774 length = x2 - x1;
1775 } else {
1776 thickness = x2 - x1;
1777 length = y2 - y1;
1778 }
1779 // FIXME: We really would like this check to be an ASSERT as we don't want to draw empty borders. However
1780 // nothing guarantees that the following recursive calls to drawLineForBoxSide will have non-null dimensions.
1781 if (!thickness || !length)
1782 return;
1783
1784 float deviceScaleFactor = document().deviceScaleFactor();
1785 if (borderStyle == BorderStyle::Double && (thickness * deviceScaleFactor) < 3)
1786 borderStyle = BorderStyle::Solid;
1787
1788 switch (borderStyle) {
1789 case BorderStyle::None:
1790 case BorderStyle::Hidden:
1791 return;
1792 case BorderStyle::Dotted:
1793 case BorderStyle::Dashed: {
1794 bool wasAntialiased = graphicsContext.shouldAntialias();
1795 StrokeStyle oldStrokeStyle = graphicsContext.strokeStyle();
1796 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(antialias);
1797 graphicsContext.setStrokeColor(color);
1798 graphicsContext.setStrokeThickness(thickness);
1799 graphicsContext.setStrokeStyle(borderStyle == BorderStyle::Dashed ? DashedStroke : DottedStroke);
1800 graphicsContext.drawLine(roundPointToDevicePixels(LayoutPoint(x1, y1), deviceScaleFactor), roundPointToDevicePixels(LayoutPoint(x2, y2), deviceScaleFactor));
1801 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(wasAntialiased);
1802 graphicsContext.setStrokeStyle(oldStrokeStyle);
1803 break;
1804 }
1805 case BorderStyle::Double: {
1806 float thirdOfThickness = ceilToDevicePixel(thickness / 3, deviceScaleFactor);
1807 ASSERT(thirdOfThickness);
1808
1809 if (!adjacentWidth1 && !adjacentWidth2) {
1810 StrokeStyle oldStrokeStyle = graphicsContext.strokeStyle();
1811 graphicsContext.setStrokeStyle(NoStroke);
1812 graphicsContext.setFillColor(color);
1813
1814 bool wasAntialiased = graphicsContext.shouldAntialias();
1815 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(antialias);
1816
1817 switch (side) {
1818 case BoxSide::Top:
1819 case BoxSide::Bottom:
1820 drawBorderRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x1, y1, length, thirdOfThickness), deviceScaleFactor));
1821 drawBorderRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x1, y2 - thirdOfThickness, length, thirdOfThickness), deviceScaleFactor));
1822 break;
1823 case BoxSide::Left:
1824 case BoxSide::Right:
1825 drawBorderRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x1, y1, thirdOfThickness, length), deviceScaleFactor));
1826 drawBorderRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x2 - thirdOfThickness, y1, thirdOfThickness, length), deviceScaleFactor));
1827 break;
1828 }
1829
1830 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(wasAntialiased);
1831 graphicsContext.setStrokeStyle(oldStrokeStyle);
1832 } else {
1833 float adjacent1BigThird = ceilToDevicePixel(adjacentWidth1 / 3, deviceScaleFactor);
1834 float adjacent2BigThird = ceilToDevicePixel(adjacentWidth2 / 3, deviceScaleFactor);
1835
1836 float offset1 = floorToDevicePixel(fabs(adjacentWidth1) * 2 / 3, deviceScaleFactor);
1837 float offset2 = floorToDevicePixel(fabs(adjacentWidth2) * 2 / 3, deviceScaleFactor);
1838
1839 float mitreOffset1 = adjacentWidth1 < 0 ? offset1 : 0;
1840 float mitreOffset2 = adjacentWidth1 > 0 ? offset1 : 0;
1841 float mitreOffset3 = adjacentWidth2 < 0 ? offset2 : 0;
1842 float mitreOffset4 = adjacentWidth2 > 0 ? offset2 : 0;
1843
1844 FloatRect paintBorderRect;
1845 switch (side) {
1846 case BoxSide::Top:
1847 paintBorderRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x1 + mitreOffset1, y1, (x2 - mitreOffset3) - (x1 + mitreOffset1), thirdOfThickness), deviceScaleFactor);
1848 drawLineFor(paintBorderRect, side, BorderStyle::Solid, FloatSize(adjacent1BigThird, adjacent2BigThird));
1849
1850 paintBorderRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x1 + mitreOffset2, y2 - thirdOfThickness, (x2 - mitreOffset4) - (x1 + mitreOffset2), thirdOfThickness), deviceScaleFactor);
1851 drawLineFor(paintBorderRect, side, BorderStyle::Solid, FloatSize(adjacent1BigThird, adjacent2BigThird));
1852 break;
1853 case BoxSide::Left:
1854 paintBorderRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x1, y1 + mitreOffset1, thirdOfThickness, (y2 - mitreOffset3) - (y1 + mitreOffset1)), deviceScaleFactor);
1855 drawLineFor(paintBorderRect, side, BorderStyle::Solid, FloatSize(adjacent1BigThird, adjacent2BigThird));
1856
1857 paintBorderRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x2 - thirdOfThickness, y1 + mitreOffset2, thirdOfThickness, (y2 - mitreOffset4) - (y1 + mitreOffset2)), deviceScaleFactor);
1858 drawLineFor(paintBorderRect, side, BorderStyle::Solid, FloatSize(adjacent1BigThird, adjacent2BigThird));
1859 break;
1860 case BoxSide::Bottom:
1861 paintBorderRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x1 + mitreOffset2, y1, (x2 - mitreOffset4) - (x1 + mitreOffset2), thirdOfThickness), deviceScaleFactor);
1862 drawLineFor(paintBorderRect, side, BorderStyle::Solid, FloatSize(adjacent1BigThird, adjacent2BigThird));
1863
1864 paintBorderRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x1 + mitreOffset1, y2 - thirdOfThickness, (x2 - mitreOffset3) - (x1 + mitreOffset1), thirdOfThickness), deviceScaleFactor);
1865 drawLineFor(paintBorderRect, side, BorderStyle::Solid, FloatSize(adjacent1BigThird, adjacent2BigThird));
1866 break;
1867 case BoxSide::Right:
1868 paintBorderRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x1, y1 + mitreOffset2, thirdOfThickness, (y2 - mitreOffset4) - (y1 + mitreOffset2)), deviceScaleFactor);
1869 drawLineFor(paintBorderRect, side, BorderStyle::Solid, FloatSize(adjacent1BigThird, adjacent2BigThird));
1870
1871 paintBorderRect = snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x2 - thirdOfThickness, y1 + mitreOffset1, thirdOfThickness, (y2 - mitreOffset3) - (y1 + mitreOffset1)), deviceScaleFactor);
1872 drawLineFor(paintBorderRect, side, BorderStyle::Solid, FloatSize(adjacent1BigThird, adjacent2BigThird));
1873 break;
1874 default:
1875 break;
1876 }
1877 }
1878 break;
1879 }
1880 case BorderStyle::Ridge:
1881 case BorderStyle::Groove: {
1882 BorderStyle s1;
1883 BorderStyle s2;
1884 if (borderStyle == BorderStyle::Groove) {
1885 s1 = BorderStyle::Inset;
1886 s2 = BorderStyle::Outset;
1887 } else {
1888 s1 = BorderStyle::Outset;
1889 s2 = BorderStyle::Inset;
1890 }
1891
1892 float adjacent1BigHalf = ceilToDevicePixel(adjacentWidth1 / 2, deviceScaleFactor);
1893 float adjacent2BigHalf = ceilToDevicePixel(adjacentWidth2 / 2, deviceScaleFactor);
1894
1895 float adjacent1SmallHalf = floorToDevicePixel(adjacentWidth1 / 2, deviceScaleFactor);
1896 float adjacent2SmallHalf = floorToDevicePixel(adjacentWidth2 / 2, deviceScaleFactor);
1897
1898 float offset1 = 0;
1899 float offset2 = 0;
1900 float offset3 = 0;
1901 float offset4 = 0;
1902
1903 if (((side == BoxSide::Top || side == BoxSide::Left) && adjacentWidth1 < 0) || ((side == BoxSide::Bottom || side == BoxSide::Right) && adjacentWidth1 > 0))
1904 offset1 = floorToDevicePixel(adjacentWidth1 / 2, deviceScaleFactor);
1905
1906 if (((side == BoxSide::Top || side == BoxSide::Left) && adjacentWidth2 < 0) || ((side == BoxSide::Bottom || side == BoxSide::Right) && adjacentWidth2 > 0))
1907 offset2 = ceilToDevicePixel(adjacentWidth2 / 2, deviceScaleFactor);
1908
1909 if (((side == BoxSide::Top || side == BoxSide::Left) && adjacentWidth1 > 0) || ((side == BoxSide::Bottom || side == BoxSide::Right) && adjacentWidth1 < 0))
1910 offset3 = floorToDevicePixel(fabs(adjacentWidth1) / 2, deviceScaleFactor);
1911
1912 if (((side == BoxSide::Top || side == BoxSide::Left) && adjacentWidth2 > 0) || ((side == BoxSide::Bottom || side == BoxSide::Right) && adjacentWidth2 < 0))
1913 offset4 = ceilToDevicePixel(adjacentWidth2 / 2, deviceScaleFactor);
1914
1915 float adjustedX = ceilToDevicePixel((x1 + x2) / 2, deviceScaleFactor);
1916 float adjustedY = ceilToDevicePixel((y1 + y2) / 2, deviceScaleFactor);
1917 // Quads can't use the default snapping rect functions.
1918 x1 = roundToDevicePixel(x1, deviceScaleFactor);
1919 x2 = roundToDevicePixel(x2, deviceScaleFactor);
1920 y1 = roundToDevicePixel(y1, deviceScaleFactor);
1921 y2 = roundToDevicePixel(y2, deviceScaleFactor);
1922
1923 switch (side) {
1924 case BoxSide::Top:
1925 drawLineFor(FloatRect(FloatPoint(x1 + offset1, y1), FloatPoint(x2 - offset2, adjustedY)), side, s1, FloatSize(adjacent1BigHalf, adjacent2BigHalf));
1926 drawLineFor(FloatRect(FloatPoint(x1 + offset3, adjustedY), FloatPoint(x2 - offset4, y2)), side, s2, FloatSize(adjacent1SmallHalf, adjacent2SmallHalf));
1927 break;
1928 case BoxSide::Left:
1929 drawLineFor(FloatRect(FloatPoint(x1, y1 + offset1), FloatPoint(adjustedX, y2 - offset2)), side, s1, FloatSize(adjacent1BigHalf, adjacent2BigHalf));
1930 drawLineFor(FloatRect(FloatPoint(adjustedX, y1 + offset3), FloatPoint(x2, y2 - offset4)), side, s2, FloatSize(adjacent1SmallHalf, adjacent2SmallHalf));
1931 break;
1932 case BoxSide::Bottom:
1933 drawLineFor(FloatRect(FloatPoint(x1 + offset1, y1), FloatPoint(x2 - offset2, adjustedY)), side, s2, FloatSize(adjacent1BigHalf, adjacent2BigHalf));
1934 drawLineFor(FloatRect(FloatPoint(x1 + offset3, adjustedY), FloatPoint(x2 - offset4, y2)), side, s1, FloatSize(adjacent1SmallHalf, adjacent2SmallHalf));
1935 break;
1936 case BoxSide::Right:
1937 drawLineFor(FloatRect(FloatPoint(x1, y1 + offset1), FloatPoint(adjustedX, y2 - offset2)), side, s2, FloatSize(adjacent1BigHalf, adjacent2BigHalf));
1938 drawLineFor(FloatRect(FloatPoint(adjustedX, y1 + offset3), FloatPoint(x2, y2 - offset4)), side, s1, FloatSize(adjacent1SmallHalf, adjacent2SmallHalf));
1939 break;
1940 }
1941 break;
1942 }
1943 case BorderStyle::Inset:
1944 case BorderStyle::Outset:
1945 calculateBorderStyleColor(borderStyle, side, color);
1946 FALLTHROUGH;
1947 case BorderStyle::Solid: {
1948 StrokeStyle oldStrokeStyle = graphicsContext.strokeStyle();
1949 ASSERT(x2 >= x1);
1950 ASSERT(y2 >= y1);
1951 if (!adjacentWidth1 && !adjacentWidth2) {
1952 graphicsContext.setStrokeStyle(NoStroke);
1953 graphicsContext.setFillColor(color);
1954 bool wasAntialiased = graphicsContext.shouldAntialias();
1955 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(antialias);
1956 drawBorderRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(x1, y1, x2 - x1, y2 - y1), deviceScaleFactor));
1957 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(wasAntialiased);
1958 graphicsContext.setStrokeStyle(oldStrokeStyle);
1959 return;
1960 }
1961
1962 // FIXME: These roundings should be replaced by ASSERT(device pixel positioned) when all the callers have transitioned to device pixels.
1963 x1 = roundToDevicePixel(x1, deviceScaleFactor);
1964 y1 = roundToDevicePixel(y1, deviceScaleFactor);
1965 x2 = roundToDevicePixel(x2, deviceScaleFactor);
1966 y2 = roundToDevicePixel(y2, deviceScaleFactor);
1967
1968 Vector<FloatPoint> quad;
1969 quad.reserveInitialCapacity(4);
1970 switch (side) {
1971 case BoxSide::Top:
1972 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x1 + std::max<float>(-adjacentWidth1, 0), y1 });
1973 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x1 + std::max<float>( adjacentWidth1, 0), y2 });
1974 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x2 - std::max<float>( adjacentWidth2, 0), y2 });
1975 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x2 - std::max<float>(-adjacentWidth2, 0), y1 });
1976 break;
1977 case BoxSide::Bottom:
1978 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x1 + std::max<float>( adjacentWidth1, 0), y1 });
1979 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x1 + std::max<float>(-adjacentWidth1, 0), y2 });
1980 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x2 - std::max<float>(-adjacentWidth2, 0), y2 });
1981 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x2 - std::max<float>( adjacentWidth2, 0), y1 });
1982 break;
1983 case BoxSide::Left:
1984 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x1, y1 + std::max<float>(-adjacentWidth1, 0) });
1985 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x1, y2 - std::max<float>(-adjacentWidth2, 0) });
1986 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x2, y2 - std::max<float>( adjacentWidth2, 0) });
1987 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x2, y1 + std::max<float>( adjacentWidth1, 0) });
1988 break;
1989 case BoxSide::Right:
1990 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x1, y1 + std::max<float>( adjacentWidth1, 0) });
1991 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x1, y2 - std::max<float>( adjacentWidth2, 0) });
1992 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x2, y2 - std::max<float>(-adjacentWidth2, 0) });
1993 quad.uncheckedAppend({ x2, y1 + std::max<float>(-adjacentWidth1, 0) });
1994 break;
1995 }
1996
1997 graphicsContext.setStrokeStyle(NoStroke);
1998 graphicsContext.setFillColor(color);
1999 bool wasAntialiased = graphicsContext.shouldAntialias();
2000 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(antialias);
2001 graphicsContext.fillPath(Path::polygonPathFromPoints(quad));
2002 graphicsContext.setShouldAntialias(wasAntialiased);
2003
2004 graphicsContext.setStrokeStyle(oldStrokeStyle);
2005 break;
2006 }
2007 }
2008}

2055void RenderElement::paintFocusRing(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const RenderStyle& style, const Vector<LayoutRect>& focusRingRects)
2056{
2057 ASSERT(style.outlineStyleIsAuto() == OutlineIsAuto::On);
2058 float outlineOffset = style.outlineOffset();
2059 Vector<FloatRect> pixelSnappedFocusRingRects;
2060 float deviceScaleFactor = document().deviceScaleFactor();
2061 for (auto rect : focusRingRects) {
2062 rect.inflate(outlineOffset);
2063 pixelSnappedFocusRingRects.append(snapRectToDevicePixels(rect, deviceScaleFactor));
2064 }
2065 Color focusRingColor = usePlatformFocusRingColorForOutlineStyleAuto() ? RenderTheme::singleton().focusRingColor(styleColorOptions()) : style.visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyOutlineColor);
2066 bool needsRepaint;
2067 if (useShrinkWrappedFocusRingForOutlineStyleAuto() && style.hasBorderRadius()) {
2068 Path path = PathUtilities::pathWithShrinkWrappedRectsForOutline(pixelSnappedFocusRingRects, style.border(), outlineOffset, style.direction(), style.writingMode(),
2069 document().deviceScaleFactor());
2070 if (path.isEmpty()) {
2071 for (auto rect : pixelSnappedFocusRingRects)
2072 path.addRect(rect);
2073 }
2074 needsRepaint = drawFocusRing(paintInfo.context(), page(), path, style, focusRingColor);
2075 } else
2076 needsRepaint = drawFocusRing(paintInfo.context(), page(), pixelSnappedFocusRingRects, style, focusRingColor);
2077 if (needsRepaint)
2078 page().focusController().setFocusedElementNeedsRepaint();
2079}
