2081void RenderElement::paintOutline(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutRect& paintRect)
2082{
2083 GraphicsContext& graphicsContext = paintInfo.context();
2084 if (graphicsContext.paintingDisabled())
2085 return;
2086
2087 if (!hasOutline())
2088 return;
2089
2090 auto& styleToUse = style();
2091 float outlineWidth = floorToDevicePixel(styleToUse.outlineWidth(), document().deviceScaleFactor());
2092 float outlineOffset = floorToDevicePixel(styleToUse.outlineOffset(), document().deviceScaleFactor());
2093
2094 // Only paint the focus ring by hand if the theme isn't able to draw it.
2095 if (styleToUse.outlineStyleIsAuto() == OutlineIsAuto::On && !theme().supportsFocusRing(styleToUse)) {
2096 Vector<LayoutRect> focusRingRects;
2097 LayoutRect paintRectToUse { paintRect };
2098 if (is<RenderBox>(*this))
2099 paintRectToUse = theme().adjustedPaintRect(downcast<RenderBox>(*this), paintRectToUse);
2100 addFocusRingRects(focusRingRects, paintRectToUse.location(), paintInfo.paintContainer);
2101 paintFocusRing(paintInfo, styleToUse, focusRingRects);
2102 }
2103
2104 if (hasOutlineAnnotation() && styleToUse.outlineStyleIsAuto() == OutlineIsAuto::Off && !theme().supportsFocusRing(styleToUse))
2105 addPDFURLRect(paintInfo, paintRect.location());
2106
2107 if (styleToUse.outlineStyleIsAuto() == OutlineIsAuto::On || styleToUse.outlineStyle() == BorderStyle::None)
2108 return;
2109
2110 FloatRect outer = paintRect;
2111 outer.inflate(outlineOffset + outlineWidth);
2112 FloatRect inner = outer;
2113 inner.inflate(-outlineWidth);
2114
2115 // FIXME: This prevents outlines from painting inside the object. See bug 12042
2116 if (outer.isEmpty())
2117 return;
2118
2119 BorderStyle outlineStyle = styleToUse.outlineStyle();
2120 Color outlineColor = styleToUse.visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyOutlineColor);
2121
2122 bool useTransparencyLayer = !outlineColor.isOpaque();
2123 if (useTransparencyLayer) {
2124 if (outlineStyle == BorderStyle::Solid) {
2125 Path path;
2126 path.addRect(outer);
2127 path.addRect(inner);
2128 graphicsContext.setFillRule(WindRule::EvenOdd);
2129 graphicsContext.setFillColor(outlineColor);
2130 graphicsContext.fillPath(path);
2131 return;
2132 }
2133 graphicsContext.beginTransparencyLayer(outlineColor.alphaAsFloat());
2134 outlineColor = outlineColor.opaqueColor();
2135 }
2136
2137 float leftOuter = outer.x();
2138 float leftInner = inner.x();
2139 float rightOuter = outer.maxX();
2140 float rightInner = std::min(inner.maxX(), rightOuter);
2141 float topOuter = outer.y();
2142 float topInner = inner.y();
2143 float bottomOuter = outer.maxY();
2144 float bottomInner = std::min(inner.maxY(), bottomOuter);
2145
2146 drawLineForBoxSide(graphicsContext, FloatRect(FloatPoint(leftOuter, topOuter), FloatPoint(leftInner, bottomOuter)), BoxSide::Left, outlineColor, outlineStyle, outlineWidth, outlineWidth);
2147 drawLineForBoxSide(graphicsContext, FloatRect(FloatPoint(leftOuter, topOuter), FloatPoint(rightOuter, topInner)), BoxSide::Top, outlineColor, outlineStyle, outlineWidth, outlineWidth);
2148 drawLineForBoxSide(graphicsContext, FloatRect(FloatPoint(rightInner, topOuter), FloatPoint(rightOuter, bottomOuter)), BoxSide::Right, outlineColor, outlineStyle, outlineWidth, outlineWidth);
2149 drawLineForBoxSide(graphicsContext, FloatRect(FloatPoint(leftOuter, bottomInner), FloatPoint(rightOuter, bottomOuter)), BoxSide::Bottom, outlineColor, outlineStyle, outlineWidth, outlineWidth);
2150
2151 if (useTransparencyLayer)
2152 graphicsContext.endTransparencyLayer();
2153}

2212void RenderElement::adjustFragmentedFlowStateOnContainingBlockChangeIfNeeded()
2213{
2214 if (fragmentedFlowState() == NotInsideFragmentedFlow)
2215 return;
2216
2217 // Invalidate the containing block caches.
2218 if (is<RenderBlock>(*this))
2219 downcast<RenderBlock>(*this).resetEnclosingFragmentedFlowAndChildInfoIncludingDescendants();
2220 else {
2221 // Relatively positioned inline boxes can have absolutely positioned block descendants. We need to reset them as well.
2222 for (auto& descendant : descendantsOfType<RenderBlock>(*this))
2223 descendant.resetEnclosingFragmentedFlowAndChildInfoIncludingDescendants();
2224 }
2225
2226 // Adjust the flow tread state on the subtree.
2227 setFragmentedFlowState(RenderObject::computedFragmentedFlowState(*this));
2228 for (auto& descendant : descendantsOfType<RenderObject>(*this))
2229 descendant.setFragmentedFlowState(RenderObject::computedFragmentedFlowState(descendant));
2230}
2231
2232void RenderElement::removeFromRenderFragmentedFlow()
2233{
2234 ASSERT(fragmentedFlowState() != NotInsideFragmentedFlow);
2235 // Sometimes we remove the element from the flow, but it's not destroyed at that time.
2236 // It's only until later when we actually destroy it and remove all the children from it.
2237 // Currently, that happens for firstLetter elements and list markers.
2238 // Pass in the flow thread so that we don't have to look it up for all the children.
2239 removeFromRenderFragmentedFlowIncludingDescendants(true);
2240}
2241
2242void RenderElement::removeFromRenderFragmentedFlowIncludingDescendants(bool shouldUpdateState)
2243{
2244 // Once we reach another flow thread we don't need to update the flow thread state
2245 // but we have to continue cleanup the flow thread info.
2246 if (isRenderFragmentedFlow())
2247 shouldUpdateState = false;
2248
2249 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<RenderObject>(*this)) {
2250 if (is<RenderElement>(child)) {
2251 downcast<RenderElement>(child).removeFromRenderFragmentedFlowIncludingDescendants(shouldUpdateState);
2252 continue;
2253 }
2254 if (shouldUpdateState)
2255 child.setFragmentedFlowState(NotInsideFragmentedFlow);
2256 }
2257
2258 // We have to ask for our containing flow thread as it may be above the removed sub-tree.
2259 RenderFragmentedFlow* enclosingFragmentedFlow = this->enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2260 while (enclosingFragmentedFlow) {
2261 enclosingFragmentedFlow->removeFlowChildInfo(*this);
2262
2263 if (enclosingFragmentedFlow->fragmentedFlowState() == NotInsideFragmentedFlow)
2264 break;
2265 auto* parent = enclosingFragmentedFlow->parent();
2266 if (!parent)
2267 break;
2268 enclosingFragmentedFlow = parent->enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2269 }
2270 if (is<RenderBlock>(*this))
2271 downcast<RenderBlock>(*this).setCachedEnclosingFragmentedFlowNeedsUpdate();
2272
2273 if (shouldUpdateState)
2274 setFragmentedFlowState(NotInsideFragmentedFlow);
2275}
2276
2277void RenderElement::resetEnclosingFragmentedFlowAndChildInfoIncludingDescendants(RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow)
2278{
2279 if (fragmentedFlow)
2280 fragmentedFlow->removeFlowChildInfo(*this);
2281
2282 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<RenderElement>(*this))
2283 child.resetEnclosingFragmentedFlowAndChildInfoIncludingDescendants(fragmentedFlow);
2284}

2287static RenderObject::BlockContentHeightType includeNonFixedHeight(const RenderObject& renderer)
2288{

2302
2303void RenderElement::adjustComputedFontSizesOnBlocks(float size, float visibleWidth)
2304{
2305 Document* document = view().frameView().frame().document();
2306 if (!document)
2307 return;
2308
2309 Vector<int> depthStack;
2310 int currentDepth = 0;
2311 int newFixedDepth = 0;
2312
2313 // We don't apply autosizing to nodes with fixed height normally.
2314 // But we apply it to nodes which are located deep enough
2315 // (nesting depth is greater than some const) inside of a parent block
2316 // which has fixed height but its content overflows intentionally.
2317 for (RenderObject* descendent = traverseNext(this, includeNonFixedHeight, currentDepth, newFixedDepth); descendent; descendent = descendent->traverseNext(this, includeNonFixedHeight, currentDepth, newFixedDepth)) {
2318 while (depthStack.size() > 0 && currentDepth <= depthStack[depthStack.size() - 1])
2319 depthStack.remove(depthStack.size() - 1);
2320 if (newFixedDepth)
2321 depthStack.append(newFixedDepth);
2322
2323 int stackSize = depthStack.size();
2324 if (is<RenderBlockFlow>(*descendent) && !descendent->isListItem() && (!stackSize || currentDepth - depthStack[stackSize - 1] > TextAutoSizingFixedHeightDepth))
2325 downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*descendent).adjustComputedFontSizes(size, visibleWidth);
2326 newFixedDepth = 0;
2327 }
2328
2329 // Remove style from auto-sizing table that are no longer valid.
2330 document->textAutoSizing().updateRenderTree();
2331}
2332
2333void RenderElement::resetTextAutosizing()
2334{
2335 Document* document = view().frameView().frame().document();
2336 if (!document)
2337 return;
2338
2339 LOG(TextAutosizing, "RenderElement::resetTextAutosizing()");
2340
2341 document->textAutoSizing().reset();
2342
2343 Vector<int> depthStack;
2344 int currentDepth = 0;
2345 int newFixedDepth = 0;
2346
2347 for (RenderObject* descendent = traverseNext(this, includeNonFixedHeight, currentDepth, newFixedDepth); descendent; descendent = descendent->traverseNext(this, includeNonFixedHeight, currentDepth, newFixedDepth)) {
2348 while (depthStack.size() > 0 && currentDepth <= depthStack[depthStack.size() - 1])
2349 depthStack.remove(depthStack.size() - 1);
2350 if (newFixedDepth)
2351 depthStack.append(newFixedDepth);
2352
2353 int stackSize = depthStack.size();
2354 if (is<RenderBlockFlow>(*descendent) && !descendent->isListItem() && (!stackSize || currentDepth - depthStack[stackSize - 1] > TextAutoSizingFixedHeightDepth))
2355 downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*descendent).resetComputedFontSize();
2356 newFixedDepth = 0;
2357 }
2358}

2361std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> RenderElement::animatedStyle()
2362{
2363 std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> result;
2364
2365 if (auto* timeline = documentTimeline())
2366 result = timeline->animatedStyleForRenderer(*this);
